363
00:38:41,250 --> 00:38:45,190
People cower in fear at the
mention of the organizer’s name.

364
00:38:45,470 --> 00:38:47,090
So who would dare arrest him?

365
00:38:57,180 --> 00:38:58,380
What the fuck?

366
00:38:58,710 --> 00:39:03,840
Do you know the golden rule is to
never mention the race in public?

367
00:39:27,020 --> 00:39:29,360
What’s the matter, P’ Payu?
Bad mood?

368
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:34,920
Or are you still upset about Ple?

369
00:39:38,490 --> 00:39:42,860
It’s nothing, I just met
some annoying people.

370
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:45,200
But I already dealt with them.

371
00:39:48,220 --> 00:39:49,710
So you’re not angry with me anymore.

372
00:39:51,880 --> 00:39:53,420
When did I ever get angry with you?

373
00:39:54,840 --> 00:39:57,910
When you told your best friend about us...

374
00:39:59,340 --> 00:40:00,850
I couldn’t have been happier.

375
00:40:04,390 --> 00:40:05,550
So...

376
00:40:07,170 --> 00:40:09,140
Why would you think I’d keep it a secret?

377
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:21,940
I assumed you were afraid that
the way he looked at you would change.

378
00:40:23,800 --> 00:40:24,850
That’s true.

379
00:40:25,640 --> 00:40:29,930
I was afraid Sky would change
because I suddenly liked a guy.

380
00:40:30,940 --> 00:40:34,220
But I planned to tell him anyway.

381
00:40:35,520 --> 00:40:40,110
If he didn’t understand,
I’d keep pestering him until he did.

382
00:40:45,030 --> 00:40:46,710
Because I’ve chosen both choices...

383
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:50,820
Whether it’s being your wife
or having you as my husband.

384
00:40:52,630 --> 00:40:57,550
No matter how much you bully me,
I won’t break up with you.

385
00:40:59,910 --> 00:41:03,160
I tried so hard.
I’ll be a fool if I let you go.

386
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:05,170
Right?

387
00:41:18,660 --> 00:41:20,940
Mama, this is Payu.

388
00:41:21,930 --> 00:41:25,230
Please allow Rain to sleep
over at my house tonight.

389
00:41:27,400 --> 00:41:28,400
Yes.

390
00:41:29,430 --> 00:41:30,480
Thank you.

391
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:39,660
Let’s go home.

392
00:41:42,540 --> 00:41:44,480
Please.

393
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:46,290
Come home with me.

394
00:41:48,060 --> 00:41:49,300
You're cheating.

395
00:44:01,130 --> 00:44:02,140
Hungry?

396
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:03,970
Don’t stop.

397
00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:07,930
You wanna hear me sing?

398
00:44:11,570 --> 00:44:12,570
Okay.

399
00:44:13,350 --> 00:44:14,700
But there are conditions.

400
00:44:16,170 --> 00:44:19,970
You’ve still got conditions?
I’m already dog-tired because of you.

401
00:44:20,210 --> 00:44:23,640
Can’t you just be obedient and do as I say?

402
00:44:25,750 --> 00:44:27,480
You need to get some exercise.

403
00:44:27,840 --> 00:44:31,840
I’ll make you roll a car tire
around the garage for 10 laps.

404
00:44:35,500 --> 00:44:36,660
So what’s your decision?

405
00:44:37,850 --> 00:44:39,340
Do you wanna hear my voice?

406
00:44:54,250 --> 00:44:57,200
There are two rules
that you need to follow.

407
00:44:58,120 --> 00:45:01,680
Rule No.1: Look into my eyes.

408
00:45:02,930 --> 00:45:05,770
Rule No.2: Don’t turn your face away.

409
00:45:11,050 --> 00:45:12,160
Can I blink?

410
00:45:14,850 --> 00:45:17,890
Yes, you can blink.

411
00:45:19,570 --> 00:45:21,850
But you must look at me the whole time.

412
00:45:31,600 --> 00:45:34,580
Do you know how good things are?

413
00:45:34,680 --> 00:45:37,760
Do you know how happy I am?

414
00:45:37,850 --> 00:45:44,110
Do you know how much
my old life has changed?

415
00:45:44,220 --> 00:45:50,440
Do you know how I was before I met you?

416
00:45:50,510 --> 00:45:58,510
Do you know how significant
it is to have met you?

417
00:46:01,070 --> 00:46:02,950
You...

418
00:46:03,740 --> 00:46:08,170
You are everything...

419
00:46:10,370 --> 00:46:16,360
That makes my life memorable.

420
00:46:18,070 --> 00:46:21,990
Ever since I met you.

421
00:46:25,330 --> 00:46:31,180
Thank heaven for bringing us together.

422
00:46:31,570 --> 00:46:37,630
Thank the Man Upstairs
that brought you to me.

423
00:46:38,200 --> 00:46:41,460
Thank all those fateful events.

424
00:46:41,640 --> 00:46:48,130
Because they led me to...

425
00:46:50,190 --> 00:46:54,540
You, my darling.

426
00:46:58,130 --> 00:47:04,760
Thank heaven for bringing us together.

427
00:47:05,010 --> 00:47:11,460
Thank the Man Upstairs
that brought you to me.

428
00:47:12,050 --> 00:47:15,250
Thank all those fateful events.

429
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:22,040
Because they led me to...

430
00:47:24,810 --> 00:47:29,420
You, my darling.

431
00:47:31,370 --> 00:47:32,410
Wait!

432
00:47:33,020 --> 00:47:35,900
Time out! You’re cheating.

433
00:47:39,710 --> 00:47:41,940
You’ve lost.

434
00:47:44,310 --> 00:47:45,980
It’d be a miracle if I won.

435
00:47:47,020 --> 00:47:49,550
And I didn’t wanna compete against you.

436
00:47:52,710 --> 00:47:56,370
So it means that I won.

437
00:47:57,950 --> 00:47:59,040
Right?

438
00:48:04,050 --> 00:48:05,140
My darling.

439
00:48:10,380 --> 00:48:11,700
You’re cheating, P’ Payu.

440
00:48:39,870 --> 00:48:41,290
Here, I’ll feed you.

441
00:48:47,590 --> 00:48:51,000
Aren’t you just adorable?

442
00:48:52,880 --> 00:48:56,330
Bro, did you forget I was here too?

443
00:48:57,480 --> 00:49:00,790
So when are you gonna move out?

444
00:49:02,060 --> 00:49:04,400
This house is a shared inheritance.

445
00:49:05,810 --> 00:49:08,980
Right, why don’t you
bring Rain to the next race?

446
00:49:16,820 --> 00:49:18,120
Too many assholes.

447
00:49:19,390 --> 00:49:22,980
They’re just a bunch of rich kids
who wanna show off.

448
00:49:23,620 --> 00:49:26,370
They’ll get banned if they make trouble.

449
00:49:27,360 --> 00:49:30,780
You know how much P’ Pakin
hates troublemakers.

450
00:49:33,230 --> 00:49:37,460
And you’re his favorite guy.
So you can just bring Rain with you.

451
00:49:44,320 --> 00:49:46,980
Don’t you want Rain to see your world?

452
00:49:49,270 --> 00:49:53,420
P’ Payu, please take me to the race.
I wanna watch it.

453
00:49:55,580 --> 00:49:58,770
Fine, but don’t sneak in like that again.

454
00:50:00,610 --> 00:50:05,590
And if anyone asks,
just say that you’re P’ Payu’s wife.

455
00:50:12,560 --> 00:50:13,750
I'm gonna eat.

456
00:50:15,230 --> 00:50:16,410
Try this dish.

457
00:50:32,480 --> 00:50:34,130
Can I really come here?

458
00:50:35,560 --> 00:50:37,120
Just do as I said.

459
00:50:40,930 --> 00:50:43,200
Oh, you mean that?

460
00:50:46,830 --> 00:50:53,800
So if anyone asks,
I can say that I’m your wife, right?

461
00:50:55,310 --> 00:50:57,250
You already know that.

462
00:51:03,610 --> 00:51:07,260
Last time I sneaked in,
I didn’t pay attention.

463
00:51:07,860 --> 00:51:11,200
But to be able to close a road,
P’ Pakin’s really something.

464
00:51:15,510 --> 00:51:16,340
That’s right.

465
00:51:18,360 --> 00:51:20,990
